"{\"uid\": \"forbes.com-sites-kaseynelson-2024-07-30-team-usa-takeover-us-womens-gymnastics-grabs-2024-olympic-team-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByKasey Nelson,  Former Contributor.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 36, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nelson_Muntz\", \"score\": 0.9999225454287364, \"rank\": 7.74546356620696e-05, \"text\": \"Nelson\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nelson_Muntz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nelson_Muntz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Redemption tastes sweet for the U.S. women's gymnastics team, winning the Olympic gold medal in the gymnastics team final inside of Bercy Arena in Paris on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 38, \"to\": 202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 170, \"end\": 181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bercy Arena\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\"}, {\"begin\": 185, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999877218, \"rank\": 1.2217763024975153e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The veteran gymnasts on the squad had labeled this Olympic Games their \\\"redemption tour\\\" after winning silver in the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. scored 171.296 to win gold, while Italy took silver (165.494), their first Olympic team medal since 1928, and Brazil finished with the bronze (164.497).\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 377, \"end\": 382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9995484641740382, \"rank\": 0.0004471872254646681, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 453, \"end\": 459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7400040655271588, \"rank\": 0.35130634390494947, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles also made U.S. gymnastics history on Tuesday with her eighth Olympic medal, surpassing Shannon Miller.\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 592, \"end\": 606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shannon_Miller\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0065052996959892e-71, \"text\": \"Shannon Miller\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shannon_Miller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shannon_Miller\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to Biles, a three-time Olympian and Rio all-around champion, the U.S. team relied heavily on two-time Olympians Suni Lee (Tokyo all-around champion) and Jordan Chiles (Tokyo Team Silver) and Jade Carey (Tokyo floor champion).\", \"from\": 608, \"to\": 845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 643, \"end\": 651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999979495442, \"rank\": 2.050336020603153e-09, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995943654, \"rank\": 4.055724727183741e-10, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 732, \"end\": 740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suni Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 742, \"end\": 747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 2.9024771783799468e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 773, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 811, \"end\": 821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jade Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\"}, {\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 2.9024771783799468e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles and Chiles competed all-around, Suni Lee on bars, beam, and floor and Carey on vault.\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 922, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.535337270131176e-20, \"text\": \"Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Newcomer Hezly Rivera was not put in any of the four lineups.\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 1000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 954, \"end\": 960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariano_Rivera\", \"score\": 0.9999998636699368, \"rank\": 1.2053288390648183e-07, \"text\": \"Rivera\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariano_Rivera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariano_Rivera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For scoring in the women's gymnastics team final, each team puts up three athletes and every score counts toward the team total.\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. began on vault and rotated in Olympic order (vault, bars, beam and floor).\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1214, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy also started on vault, and Brazil and China began on bars.\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9995484641740382, \"rank\": 0.0004471872254646681, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7400040655271588, \"rank\": 0.35130634390494947, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1259, \"end\": 1264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.7910361531980709, \"rank\": 0.2421296311951725, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First up was Chiles on vault, performing a Yurchenko double-full and earning a 14.4 to mark a great start for the U.S. team.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Carey launched a Cheng vault (half onto the table front 1.5 twist off) with only a hop in place for a huge 14.8.\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1406, \"end\": 1411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.535337270131176e-20, \"text\": \"Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Biles decided against the Biles II due to calf issues, she competed the Cheng vault with a hop back on the landing for a 14.9 to lead the way for Team USA.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1671, \"end\": 1679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999474793689921, \"rank\": 5.252326949216113e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. takes an early lead after rotation one, with China in second and Italy in third.\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.7910361531980709, \"rank\": 0.2421296311951725, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1755, \"end\": 1760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9995484641740382, \"rank\": 0.0004471872254646681, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Onto rotation two, Chiles led off again for the U.S. on uneven bars, showing off her stunning lines and nearly sticking her full-twisting double back dismount (14.366).\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowd erupted as she shouted,\\\"Let us go!\\\"\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles also hit her bar set, dismounting with a double-double back for a 14.4.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last up for the U.S., Lee performed a huge Nabieva (toe on Tkatchev layout) to Bhardwaj (full-twisting pac salto) but hit her feet on the mat for a five-tenth deduction.\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2087, \"end\": 2090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999963933988, \"rank\": 3.606693984945859e-09, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 2108, \"end\": 2115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tatiana_Nabieva\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nabieva\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tatiana_Nabieva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tatiana_Nabieva\"}, {\"begin\": 2124, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glossary_of_gymnastics_terms\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.33214961528062e-67, \"text\": \"Tkatchev\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glossary_of_gymnastics_terms\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glossary_of_gymnastics_terms\"}, {\"begin\": 2144, \"end\": 2152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vishal_Bhardwaj\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bhardwaj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vishal_Bhardwaj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vishal_Bhardwaj\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was able to stay on the equipment with no falls and finished with a full-twisting double back to still lead the way for Team USA with a 14.566.\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2359, \"end\": 2367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999474793689921, \"rank\": 5.252326949216113e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. women increased their lead by 3.102 after falling on beam from both Brazil and China.\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7400040655271588, \"rank\": 0.35130634390494947, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2472, \"end\": 2477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.7910361531980709, \"rank\": 0.2421296311951725, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China's Zhou Yaqin suffered two falls, and Brazil's Julia Soares also fell for a 12.4.\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2565, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2479, \"end\": 2484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.7910361531980709, \"rank\": 0.2421296311951725, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2487, \"end\": 2491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhou_dynasty\", \"score\": 0.8870446895134068, \"rank\": 0.10887398497755463, \"text\": \"Zhou\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhou_dynasty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhou_dynasty\"}, {\"begin\": 2492, \"end\": 2497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaqeen\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yaqin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaqeen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaqeen\"}, {\"begin\": 2522, \"end\": 2528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7400040655271588, \"rank\": 0.35130634390494947, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2531, \"end\": 2536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"score\": 0.9999956711847533, \"rank\": 4.328577635379936e-06, \"text\": \"Julia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brazil's Rebeca Andrade felt the pressure with a big wobble but stayed on for a 14.133.\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2566, \"end\": 2572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7400040655271588, \"rank\": 0.35130634390494947, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebeca Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the third rotation, Chiles began on beam with a fall on her front pike mount (one-point deduction) but finished the routine strong with a stuck double pike dismount.\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She scored a 12.733, which was not the beam start Team USA was looking for.\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2874, \"end\": 2882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999474793689921, \"rank\": 5.252326949216113e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pressure was on Lee for a must-hit routine.\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 2947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2920, \"end\": 2923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999963933988, \"rank\": 3.606693984945859e-09, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She came up clutch for Team USA, hitting a stunning routine, including a side aerial to a layout, with no wobbles in sight.\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 3071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2971, \"end\": 2979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999474793689921, \"rank\": 5.252326949216113e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee fired a 14.6 to get the U.S. back on track.\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3072, \"end\": 3075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999963933988, \"rank\": 3.606693984945859e-09, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles exuded confidence and hit her beam set.\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She had a wobble on her side aerial but stayed on and dismounted with a big back handspring, back handspring two-foot to full-in dismount earning a 14.366 to put Team USA back on top.\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3328, \"end\": 3336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999474793689921, \"rank\": 5.252326949216113e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy finished the rotation in second while Great Britain surged to third.\", \"from\": 3350, \"to\": 3424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3350, \"end\": 3355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9995484641740382, \"rank\": 0.0004471872254646681, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3394, \"end\": 3407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9851326306737803, \"rank\": 0.009631579714768987, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. women headed to their fourth and final rotation with a commanding lead.\", \"from\": 3426, \"to\": 3506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee led off on floor with a stunning routine, including a double-double laid out, 1.5 twist to front full, and double back as the crowd went wild.\", \"from\": 3507, \"to\": 3653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3507, \"end\": 3510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999963933988, \"rank\": 3.606693984945859e-09, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She earned a 13.533.\", \"from\": 3654, \"to\": 3674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chiles added energy into the arena with her Beyonc\\u00e9-themed routine that had the crowd clapping to the music with a full-twisting double layout, front-full step out to full-in.\", \"from\": 3675, \"to\": 3850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished with a double layout and saluted in tears of joy, scoring a 13.966.\", \"from\": 3851, \"to\": 3931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles closed out for the U.S. with her Taylor Swift, \\\"Are you ready for it?\\\"\", \"fro